<TITLE> Heart of gold </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Nov 22 (bdnews24.com)  Television images of the destruction wrought by cyclone Sidr has moved a poor Turkish woman to donate her collection of bangles to the relief effort. The act of compassion came from a lower-middle class woman who took her jewellery to the Bangladesh mission in Ankara as a contribution to the relief effort. Embassy officials said they failed to make her understand the complexities involved in accepting such a donation. "Despite all reasoning and explanation of the financial complexities, we failed to subside her emotion and desperation. She wished that those bangles be sent to Bangladesh," the foreign ministry said in a statement. bdn
